rComments: DONT TAKE HIS CLASS!!!! His lectures are very hard to follow because he covers random topics. He is very unorganized, gives practice problems that have lots of errors and doesnt plan out the class well. His lectures stray from the book, and his his exams cover things that he hasnt said in lecture or covered in the book. DONT TAKE HIS CLASS

Great Prof.  Really interesting, especially if you know something about the subject matter.  Bangladeshi guy who has some interesting ideas from an interesting viewpoint about develoment economics.  Highly recommended as long as you aren't a complete moron (ie the bottom 85% of econ undergrads)

This is easily the worst professor I have had. He makes the course much harder than it needs to be. Furthermore, the way he teaches econ 302 is very different from the way it is taught by the other professors(and there are alot of them). He is an extremely intelligent man, who I think expects too much from his students. Hard to understand also.

He is a horrible professor, doesn't care about his students and doesn't really cater to conflicting schedules.  His grading is ridiculously hard, not too mention what he teaches is NOT whats on the tests.  DO NOT TAKE ANY OF HIS CLASSES!

This class was pretty difficult. Make sure to do well on the first exam because after that it gets harder. The book helps a lot esspecially since it's not too easy understanding the professors lectures. The sample problems he gave helped a lot, but those were online.

Challenging class, but a great professor.  As long as you stay on top of the sample problems and go to lecture, you'll do fine.  The exam questions are taken directly from the homework sets, so don't necessarily worry about staying on top of reading the book (although it does help).

Prof Rashid speaks with a slight accent, but I had no problem understanding him. He goes over concepts in class and asks for some math solving during tests,which is somewhat unfair but the math is mostly really easy. Show up to class and make sure you do all the problems sets and understand them and you'll ace the class. He is very good teacher, bu

Extremely disappointed with how he conducted the class.  Gave his first exam 2 weeks into class.  Essay question was ridiculous.  He went over this same question on the 1ST DAY of class AFTER he solicited the option for students to leave early.  Take Econ 300 with a different professor.
Professor Rashid was very good at answering student questions. He was very approachable. Tests were difficult but fair. I reccomend going to class because class examples often appeared on exams.

Puts lots of examples on the board that make sense, but fails to make students grasp underlying concepts.  There are too many examples to memorize, and since the tests are on application of concepts it is extermely difficult. Very knowledgable though, and is extremely good at answering questions.
Very good teacher.  Easiest out of all the Econ 300 teachers.  Very limited and basic calc.  I would recomend him over all other 300 teachers.
